WEBVTT

00:04.100 --> 00:07.100
        Cheers <i>is filmed</i>        
 <i>before a live studio audience.</i> 

00:07.100 --> 00:08.100
         ( <i>chuckling</i> )          

00:08.100 --> 00:10.100
 Well, that cute little dimple? 

00:10.200 --> 00:11.300
                 Well, I think  
                 I still got it.

00:11.400 --> 00:13.000
        It's kind of hard for   
        me to see back there.   

00:13.000 --> 00:14.900
                    ( <i>laughing</i> )

00:14.900 --> 00:18.400
  Um, Renee, I'm going to have  
      to get back to you.       

00:18.400 --> 00:20.000
         Yeah, bye-bye.         

00:20.000 --> 00:21.800
     Uh, Linda, sweetheart,     

00:21.800 --> 00:23.700
             uh, can we continue
             this over lunch?   

00:23.800 --> 00:26.000
     Well, um, your place.      

00:26.000 --> 00:27.000
          Don't cook.           

00:27.000 --> 00:28.600
          ( <i>laughing</i> )          

00:31.000 --> 00:33.100
 Let me guess-- personal call?  

00:33.200 --> 00:34.900
             Very.              

00:35.000 --> 00:37.700
     Malone, I find winking     
         really smarmy.         

00:37.700 --> 00:40.300
  Yeah, but beneath this smarm  
    is a lot of charm,          

00:40.300 --> 00:42.300
and I think you know that.      

00:43.100 --> 00:44.800
         I know this...         

00:44.800 --> 00:47.600
            I want you out      
            of my office now.   

00:47.600 --> 00:49.600
All right, all right.           
I'm sorry.                      

00:49.600 --> 00:52.000
I know I'm not supposed         
to get personal calls here,     

00:52.100 --> 00:53.900
  but what the hey, you know;   
      super-strength Sammy      

00:54.000 --> 00:55.700
  has been off the shelves now  
    for over a year--           

00:55.700 --> 00:57.400
there's a lot of pent-up demand 
        out there.              

00:58.900 --> 01:00.200
What can I say?                 

01:00.300 --> 01:01.900
            Say, "I'd better    
            get back to work.   

01:02.000 --> 01:04.099
  I don't want to get fired."   

01:04.099 --> 01:05.900
          You're cute           
     when you're humorless.     

01:05.900 --> 01:06.800
Did you know that?              

01:06.800 --> 01:08.300
      ( <i>telephone rings</i> )       

01:08.400 --> 01:10.100
            Cheers.             

01:10.200 --> 01:11.400
     No, Simone, I'm sorry.     

01:11.400 --> 01:12.400
                  Sam's working.

01:12.400 --> 01:13.700
        ( <i>whispering</i> ):         
Simone? Wait, wait, wait.       

01:13.700 --> 01:15.400
     Try him later at home.     

01:16.400 --> 01:17.400
      Well, then, perhaps       

01:17.400 --> 01:19.300
    on your next visit          
         to the States.         

01:21.700 --> 01:23.400
            Simone?             

01:23.400 --> 01:26.100
     Man, you just cost me      
    a roll in the hay.          

01:26.200 --> 01:26.700
         I owe you one.         

01:26.700 --> 01:27.800
        You're on.              

01:27.800 --> 01:29.100
      I didn't mean that.       

01:29.200 --> 01:30.800
     Wait a minute. I think     
  we need to get something...   

01:30.800 --> 01:34.800
        ( <i>piano plays</i> )         

01:34.900 --> 01:37.300
    ¶ Making your way           
      in the world today ¶      

01:37.400 --> 01:40.400
    ¶ Takes everything          
          you've got ¶          

01:40.400 --> 01:43.100
        ¶ Taking a break        
    from all your worries ¶     

01:43.100 --> 01:46.600
¶ Sure would help a lot         

01:46.600 --> 01:51.700
      ¶ Wouldn't you like       
         to get away? ¶         

01:51.700 --> 01:54.400
  ¶ Sometimes you want to go    

01:54.400 --> 01:59.900
    ¶ Where everybody           
    knows your name ¶           

01:59.900 --> 02:04.500
¶ And they're always glad       
        you came ¶              

02:04.500 --> 02:06.900
        ¶ You want to be        
      where you can see ¶       

